import random

def generate_data():
    target_materials = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'polypropylene', 'gold']
    target_thicknesses = [0.5, 2.1, 1.8, 4.2, 0.7, 1.4, 3.6, 0.9]
    pulse_widths = [150, 500, 300, 800, 200, 750, 1200, 450]
    energies = [3.2, 12.5, 5.8, 9.6, 1.9, 8.2, 6.7, 11.3]
    spot_sizes = [4.5, 3.1, 2.8, 6.2, 3.9, 3.7, 4.8, 5.4]
    intensities = [5.3e20, 7.2e20, 3.1e20, 8.5e20, 4.7e20, 6.9e20, 1.2e21, 2.1e21]
    powers = [5.0e13, 1.2e14, 3.5e13, 8.7e13, 7.0e13, 9.3e13, 2.5e14, 6.3e13]
    cutoff_energies = [6.2, 7.8, 5.4, 10.1, 4.9, 8.6, 9.3, 7.5]

    data = []
    for _ in range(25):
        target_material = random.choice(target_materials)
        thickness = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(target_thicknesses), max(target_thicknesses)] + [sum(target_thicknesses)/len(target_thicknesses)])))*(max(target_thicknesses) - min(target_thicknesses) + 1) + min(target_thicknesses)
        pulse_width = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(pulse_widths), max(pulse_widths)] + [sum(pulse_widths)/len(pulse_widths)])))*(max(pulse_widths) - min(pulse_widths) + 1) + min(pulse_widths)
        energy = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(energies), max(energies)] + [sum(energies)/len(energies)])))*(max(energies) - min(energies) + 1) + min(energies)
        spot_size = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(spot_sizes), max(spot_sizes)] + [sum(spot_sizes)/len(spot_sizes)])))*(max(spot_sizes) - min(spot_sizes) + 1) + min(spot_sizes)
        intensity = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(intensities), max(intensities)] + [sum(intensities)/len(intensities)])))*(max(intensities) - min(intensities) + 1) + min(intensities)
        power = intensity * energy
        cutoff_energy = random.uniform(*zip(map(lambda x: [x], [min(cutoff_energies), max(cutoff_energies)] + [sum(cutoff_energies)/len(cutoff_energies)])))*(max(cutoff_energies) - min(cutoff_energies) + 1) + min(cutoff_energies)
        data.append([target_material, thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])
    return data

new_data = generate_data()
print(new_data)
```
